# Byte-stability for the vendored-lock contract (M7c): REC-06's tree hash is
# over RAW worktree bytes, so an EOL-converting checkout (core.autocrlf) would
# permanently skew a vendored copy against a lock captured on an LF machine —
# reported in the same language as tamper. -text disables conversion: bytes in
# the repository are bytes on disk, on every platform. VENDOR THIS FILE with
# the tree (it is directory-scoped in the consumer: tools/baseline/.gitattributes
# governs exactly the hashed subtree). CONTRACT.md's manual-copy procedure
# names it.
* -text
